The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 4: The income tax department has asked Vodafone to explain why it should not be taxed Rs 12,000 crore for its $11.1-billion deal with Hong Kong- based Hutchison in 2007 to acquire its assets in the Indian joint venture with Essar. A show-cause notice was issued to Vodafone to levy Rs 12,000 crore tax. A spokesperson for Vodafone has confirmed the receipt of the notice.                            
	 New Delhi, June 4: Essar Oil will raise $300 million by issue of foreign currency convertible bonds on a preferential basis to promoter firm Essar Energy Holdings to fund expansion.                             
	 New Delhi, June 4: Mahindra amp; Mahindra has been shortlisted to make the final bid to acquire troubled South Korean auto maker SsangYong Motor. The Ruia group has also received the approval to submit its bid.                            
	 New Delhi, June 4: The government may lift the stockholding limit imposed on bulk consumers of sugar in July, taking into account the fall in prices over the last four months and better production outlook for the next year.                            
	 New Delhi, June 4: HDFC has relaunched its loan against property scheme, boasting attractive interest rates as low as 11 per cent with increased tenor.                                                                                                                          
